  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Local Conflict prevention and mitigation.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will be implemented in former 5 payams of Gogrial west county with warring communities of Aguok,Apuk and Kuac within Gogrial state for a period of 4 months while TOCH conducts conflict needs assessment for the entire state with its neighbouring states of Tonj and Wau which have been involved in the onset of conflict in 2017.
The proposed activities will include formation of women peace networks in the 5 payams which will include empowering of youth to help them to prevent violent conflicts and work together towards  reconciling communities through initiatives of sports for peace and conflict monitoring strategy with cattle camp youths as they are actors for peace and sometimes can be used to fight each other. 
TOCH will continue to work with former peace committees to support local dispute mediations and try to reconcile communities where possible and also work jointly with CTP to ensure that coordination mechanisms and technical support is provided to address emerging issues from the communities.</narrative>
  </description>
